    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-06-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-06-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="830"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d830">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">894.3311/180</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Japanese Ambassador (<persName type="from"
                            >Debuchi</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 100</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-06-17">June 17,
                            1933</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to my note No. 26, dated February
                    6, 1933,<note n="78" xml:id="d830fn78">Not printed.</note> I have the honor to
                    inform you that the Japanese Government have been much pleased with the courtesy
                    and hospitality which the Government and people of the United States have been
                    good enough to extend to the Japanese Training Squadron which is leaving
                    Honolulu today, the last port of call.</p>
                <p>I may further inform you that the Squadron has been given the most cordial
                    co-operation by the naval officers of the United States at each port of call,
                    which has greatly expedited its activities.</p>
                <pb facs="0859" n="757" xml:id="pg_757"/>
                <p>I wish to take this opportunity to express to you the sincere thanks of my
                    Government for the above manifestation of good will and courtesy toward the
                    Squadron.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>K. <hi rend="smallcaps">Debuchi</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
